<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-12-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-12-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="210" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d210">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5315/625.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Reid</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-12-11"><hi rend="italic">December 11,
                                    1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Reid says the foreign office has received a reply from the French
                            Government which is considered unsatisfactory and as demanding more than
                            the English can accede to, and that the foreign office has to-day
                            telegraphed representative of British group now negotiating in Paris to
                            sacrifice in favor of French sufficient mileage to make French and
                            German sections equal in length. Adds that it is hoped French foreign
                            office will accept such a compromise.</p>
                    </div>
